derivation: or (negative only) קֵצֶה; from H7096 (קָצָה); (used in a great variety of applications and idioms; compare H7093 (קֵץ))
outline:
1. end, extremity
    1. end, mouth, extremity
    2. border, outskirts
    3. the whole (condensed term for what is included within extremities)
    4. at the end of (a certain time)
kjv_def: [idiom] after, border, brim, brink, edge, end, (in-) finite, frontier, outmost coast, quarter, shore, (out-) side, [idiom] some, ut(-ter-) most (part).
